"04a_blockclosure.mst — BlockClosure (sprint_s06_detail.md's genesis tree
 lists BlockClosure and pins primitives 50-54 for it, but the doc's
 numbered 01-20 per-class list has no BlockClosure section — a gap in the
 doc. Every real (non-inlined) block send needs this early: 06's
 Integer>>timesRepeat: and 05's Number>>to:stop:do: already call aBlock
 value/value: for real, so this must load before 05."

"I am a block: code in square brackets, with its own arguments and
 temporaries, closed over the variables of its enclosing method and
 ready to run later. Evaluate me with value, value:, value:value:,
 value:value:value: or valueWithArguments:; numArgs answers how many
 arguments I expect. ensure: runs a clean-up block whether I complete
 normally or unwind; ifCurtailed: runs its block only on an unwind.
 Blocks are the currency of control flow here — conditionals, loops and
 every iteration protocol take me as an argument."

Object subclass: BlockClosure [
    value [
        <primitive: 50>
    ]
    value: a1 [
        <primitive: 51>
    ]
    value: a1 value: a2 [
        <primitive: 52>
    ]
    value: a1 value: a2 value: a3 [
        <primitive: 53>
    ]
    valueWithArguments: anArray [
        <primitive: 54>
    ]
    ensure: aBlock [
        <primitive: 60>
    ]
    ifCurtailed: aBlock [
        <primitive: 61>
    ]
    fork [
        "Strongtalk runs the receiver on a background process. MACVM is
         single-threaded, and the corpus's only #fork is progenv.html's
         comment-preload sweep (a first-page-load speedup MACVM doesn't need), so
         skip it entirely and answer self rather than block on it inline."
        ^self
    ]
]
